Say Reader, were not here given the two wingsFrom this time of parting the Empire between two Caeſars, Eaſt, and Weſt, it conſtantly remain'd ſo div • ded, to the very ruine of the Empire, whereas the Div • ſion by Conſtantin was quickly made up again; And 'tis remarkable that Conſtantin left it to three ſons, but Theod. to two only; two Wings, &c. of the great Eagle? Conſider it. But I will relate thee the ſtory more diſtinctly, with the very obſervable circumſtances attending it, in the very words (for the moſt part) of ſober and godly Mr. Simſon.
